## 1. Picsum.photos URL Pattern (confirmed, no API key required)

Deterministic seeded images follow this exact pattern:

```
https://picsum.photos/seed/{seed}/{width}/{height}
```

Examples for the 12-print catalog (using descriptive seed strings so images are aesthetically coherent):

```js
// data.js seed entries — all 800x1000 portrait for editorial prints
{ id: 1,  slug: "birch-morning",    seed: "birch",    imgUrl: "https://picsum.photos/seed/birch/800/1000"    },
{ id: 2,  slug: "granite-veil",     seed: "granite",  imgUrl: "https://picsum.photos/seed/granite/800/1000"  },
{ id: 3,  slug: "river-fog",        seed: "river",    imgUrl: "https://picsum.photos/seed/river/800/1000"    },
